aces, objects"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Output"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Final decision"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Classification label"}]}]}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Layers allow the network to build complexity step-by-step."}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "2. "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Non-linearity through activation functions"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Without hidden layers, you can only create linear decision boundaries. Hidden layers with "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "non-linear activations"}, {"type": "text", "text": " (ReLU, sigmoid, tanh) enable complex, non-linear boundaries."}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "3. "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Depth = Power"}]}, {"type": "bulletList", "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "More hidden layers → deeper network → can learn more complex functions"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "This is why \"deep learning\" uses many layers (hence \"deep\")"}]}]}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Mental Model"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Think of layers and neurons like a "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "factory assembly line"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":"}]}, {"type": "bulletList", "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Input layer"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Raw materials arrive (data features)"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Hidden layers"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Each layer processes and transforms the material into more refined forms"}]}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "- Layer 1: Basic processing (edges) - Layer 2: Intermediate assembly (shapes) - Layer 3: Complex assembly (objects)\n- "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Output layer"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Final product (prediction/classification)"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Each "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "neuron"}, {"type": "text", "text": " is like a worker on the line, doing a specific calculation and passing results forward."}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Key Takeaways"}]}, {"type": "bulletList", "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Neuron"}, {"type": "text", "text": " = single processing unit that computes weighted sum + bias + activation"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Layer"}, {"type": "text", "text": " = group of neurons working at the same level"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Three layer types"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Input (receives data), Hidden (learns patterns), Output (produces prediction)"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "MLP structure"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Input → 1+ hidden layers → Output; all fully connected"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Input layer neurons"}, {"type": "text", "text": " = number of input features"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Output layer neurons"}, {"type": "text", "text": " = problem type (1 for binary, #classes for multi-class)"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Hidden layers"}, {"type": "text", "text": " enable non-linear learning—this is what makes MLPs powerful"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Single perceptron = 1 neuron, no hidden layers; MLP = many neurons across layers"}]}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Understanding layers and neurons is essential before learning about backpropagation, activation functions, and training neural networks in Generative AI."}]}]}}